Kwara State government early Thursday morning allegedly commenced the demolition of the late Olusola Saraki’s ancestral political home, ‘Arúgbó’ compound, in Ilorin. The demolition of the building as gathered by TribuneOnline started around 4:00 a.m after the security operatives dispersed protesters including aged women within the complex vicinity on Wednesday. Sources confirmed that security operatives stormed the vicinity around 2:00 a.m, demolished the building but it was met with a protest as people around gathered to chase them away. ALSO READ: How NIGAV spiced up aviation sector with awards 22 Ibadan torture centre victims hospitalized as Oyo marks… Edo govt begins removal of illegal structures Mixed reactions as taskforce commences demolition of… BREAKING: Lakowe Ibeju-Lekki, Lagos residents cry for help… Just before the demolition, Saraki had blown hot, saying “Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRasaq has crossed his line.” According to Kwara State Police Public Relations Officer(PPRO), DSP Ajayi Jeffrey who spoke with TribuneOnline on the telephone claimed not to be part of the team that went for the demolition. “I know nothing about the demolition if at all there is any. In fact, no notice was given to my office,” he maintained.  Details later… SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
